docs.snippet: The number of failed asylum seekers who could not be repatriated from Germany because they lack valid documents jumped 71 percent in 2017 compared with the previous year, the interior ministry said on Monday.

headline.print_headline: Germany Struggles With Rising Number of Rejected Asylum Seekers Without Papers
headline.main: Germany Struggles With Rising Number of Rejected Asylum Seekers Without Papers

docs.snippet: A Kansas man pleaded guilty on Tuesday to the murder of an Indian-born engineer who was confronted about his immigration status at a bar, then fatally shot.

headline.print_headline: Man Pleads Guilty in Migrant’s Murder
headline.main: Kansas Man Pleads Guilty to Indian Immigrant’s Murder

docs.snippet: Amazon.com Inc may make a rival offer to buy Indian e-commerce firm Flipkart, which is in tie-up talks with Walmart Inc, local media reported, as the two U.S. retail giants jostle for dominance in India's booming online industry.

headline.print_headline: Amazon May Offer to Buy India's Flipkart: Report
headline.main: Amazon May Offer to Buy India's Flipkart: Report

docs.snippet: Shubhankar Sharma got his first glimpse of childhood icon Tiger Woods four years ago at the Delhi Golf Club.

headline.main: Sharma Eyes 1st Masters,' Fanboy Moment' With Tiger Woods

docs.snippet: Protesters led by India's lower-caste Dalit community on Monday set fire to police posts and blocked railway tracks as they opposed a Supreme Court ruling that bars immediate arrest of individuals accused of discriminating against them, media said...

headline.print_headline: India's Lower-Caste Dalits Lead Nationwide Protests Against Court Judgment
headline.main: India's Lower-Caste Dalits Lead Nationwide Protests Against Court Judgment

docs.snippet: South Africa will speed up visa processes and lure major conferences in an effort to boost foreign arrivals by 40 percent by 2021, its tourism minister said on Friday.

headline.main: South African Tourism Has 'Huge Growth Potential'-Minister

docs.snippet: Singapore's competition watchdog said it had reasonable grounds to suspect competition had been infringed by Uber Technologies Inc's [UBER.UL] deal to sell its operations in Southeast Asia to rival ride-hailing firm Grab.

headline.main: Singapore Watchdog Says Uber-Grab Deal May Have Infringed Competition

docs.snippet: Italian make-up group Kiko is in talks to bring in a minority investor to help fund growth in India, the Middle East and Asia and lift profitability, Chief Executive Cristina Scocchia said.

headline.main: Prosecutors Demand 16 Years Prison for Indonesian Politician
